<TextView 
    android:layout_width="fill_parent" 
    android:layout_height="wrap_content" 
    android:gravity="left"
    android:padding="3dp"
    android:text="mScan uses computer vision to covert paper forms into digital information.">
</TextView>
<TextView  
    android:layout_width="fill_parent" 
    android:layout_height="wrap_content" 
    android:gravity="left"
    android:padding="3dp"
    android:text="When photographing a form these are some guidelines you can follow in order to help prevent mScan from making mistakes:">
</TextView>
<TextView  
    android:layout_width="fill_parent" 
    android:layout_height="wrap_content" 
    android:gravity="left"
    android:padding="3dp"
    android:text="1. Make sure everything on the form is visable in the photo. Even sections that do not contain information you want to collect might contain features that help mScan align the form properly.">
</TextView>
<ImageView
    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
	android:src="@drawable/bad_picture">
</ImageView>
<TextView  
    android:layout_width="fill_parent" 
    android:layout_height="wrap_content" 
    android:gravity="left"
    android:padding="3dp"
    android:text="2. The form should take up about 80% of the screen space and be vertically aligned.">
</TextView>
<ImageView
    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
	android:src="@drawable/good_picture">
</ImageView>
<TextView  
    android:layout_width="fill_parent" 
    android:layout_height="wrap_content" 
    android:gravity="left"
    android:padding="3dp"
    android:text="3. Taking pictures in well lit locations, and avoiding shadows falling accross the form also helps.">
</TextView>
<TextView  
    android:layout_width="fill_parent" 
    android:layout_height="wrap_content" 
    android:gravity="left"
    android:padding="3dp"
    android:text="4. Finally, keep the camera as steady as possible.">
</TextView>
<TextView  
    android:layout_width="fill_parent" 
    android:layout_height="wrap_content" 
    android:gravity="left"
    android:padding="3dp"
    android:text="Using a stand like the one pictured below can make these guidelines much easier to follow.">
</TextView>
<ImageView
    android:layout_height="wrap_content"
    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
	android:src="@drawable/stand_example">
</ImageView>
<TextView  
    android:layout_width="fill_parent" 
    android:layout_height="wrap_content" 
    android:gravity="left"
    android:padding="3dp"
    android:text="@string/Instructions3">
</TextView>
<TextView  
    android:layout_width="fill_parent" 
    android:layout_height="wrap_content" 
    android:gravity="left"
    android:padding="3dp"
    android:text="@string/Instructions4">
</TextView>
